-- Bharat Petroleum Seeks Crude Oil for April Loading in Tender
-- B y   S h e r r y   S u
-- 2012-02-23T11:34:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/bharat-petroleum-seeks-crude-oil-for-april-loading-in-tender-1-.html
Bharat Petroleum Corp.,  India ’s
second-largest state-run oil refiner, issued a tender seeking to
buy crude oil for loading from April 1 to April 15, according to
a document obtained by Bloomberg News. The contract will be
awarded on Feb. 29.  Last month, the company bought 2 million barrels of
Nigerian Qua Iboe for loading in March from Exxon Mobil Corp.
and 1 million barrels of Forcados for February from Vitol Group.  Details of the Mumbai-based refiner’s requirements are:  To contact the reporter on this story:
